description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you a Registered Social Worker with an interest in young people and Mental Health?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pebble Lodge is a CQC Outstanding 10 Bed Hospital for young people aged between 12 and 18 years with significant Mental Illness who require an admission to hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a friendly and experienced MDT with nursing staff, psychology, medics, creative therapists, OT&#39;s, and activities. As part of service enhancement we are looking for an innovative and experienced social worker to join the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the role you will work directly with young people and their families and professionals at Pebble Lodge. You will use professional skills, knowledge and experience plus a range of interpersonal and communication skills to gather information in order to make a full assessment of risk, protection and social care needs of individuals and family/carers within relevant legal and statutory frameworks and agreed priorities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have the ability to form excellent professional relationships in a variety of situations and be able to provide advice and guidance to the team and external agencies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to undertake a &lt;strong&gt;Prevention and Management of Violence and Aggression&lt;/strong&gt; course and it is a condition of your employment that you successfully complete all aspects of this course; if this is not achieved you will not be able to commence working in the post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Employment in this post requires a Enhanced Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) check. The DBS levies a charge of £40 and the Trust will recover this cost in instalments from your first 3 salary payments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants who subscribe to the DBS update service and are able to present a valid DBS certificate will not incur a charge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Michael Ebbutt / Katie Butler, CAMHS Tier 4 Service Manager - Email: katie.butler1@nhs.net Telephone: 01202 584361&lt;/p&gt;
